                 <h3>Rasmi Badi (Kofta)</h3>
                 <p>Rasmi Badi (Kofta) is a popular traditional dish from the Kumaon region of Uttarakhand. It is a flavorful preparation made from fried lentil dumplings (badi) that are cooked in a rich, spicy gravy. The dish is often served as a main course, typically with rice or roti.</p>
                 <h3>Key Features:</h3>
                 <h4>1. Ingredients:</h4>
                 <p>Badi (lentil dumplings): Made from ground urad dal (black gram) or chana dal (gram lentils), mixed with spices like cumin, coriander, turmeric, and red chili powder.
   Gravy: Prepared with ingredients like onions, tomatoes, ginger, garlic, and spices such as cumin, garam masala, turmeric, and red chili.
