    Fresh coriander: Used as a garnish.
</p>
                 <h4>2. Preparation:</h4>
                 <p>- The badi (lentil dumplings) are prepared by soaking the lentils, grinding them, and then shaping them into small balls or patties. These are deep-fried until golden and crispy.
